<span class="displaytext">sigourney, ia-- with a campaign stop in keokuk county today, new mexico governor and (PARTY NAME) presidential candidate (candidate full) visited his 99th of iowa's 99 counties. joined by his wife, new mexico first lady barbara (candidate last), he held one of his signature "presidential job interviews" at the copper lantern restaurant in sigourney, answering the questions of everyday iowans. <p>"i am running the kind of grassroots campaign that iowans appreciate," governor (candidate last) said. "i have traveled to all of iowa's 99 counties, meeting with caucus-goers and talking to them one-on-one to hear their concerns and share my vision for the future." </p><p>throughout his campaign, governor (candidate last) has shown a dedication to traveling to small communities in rural and urban areas and reaching out to all iowans. </p><p>"as i travel through iowa and new hampshire, i see enthusiasm and amazing grassroots support for bill," first lady barbara (candidate last) said. "he is extremely dedicated to this campaign and to bringing change to our country. i am proud of him for having met with iowans in all 99 counties. because of it, he never is home, but his dedication is paying off." </p><p>governor (candidate last) detailed how he is the only candidate who brings both change and experience to the race. a former congressman, secretary of energy, and u.s. ambassador to the united nations and currently a two-term governor, (candidate last) consistently has produced results. </p><p>"in all 99 counties, i have met iowans looking for a presidential candidate who has the experience to bring about the change that our country so desperately needs," (candidate last) said. "i am that candidate. i have the experience to solve the very real problems facing our country. as president, i will end the war in iraq, work toward solving our energy crisis, and make sure that every american has access to health care." </p><p>at today's event in sigourney, (